HEADWORD: Podophyllin
<hw>Pod`o*phyl"lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Podophyllum</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A brown bitter gum
extracted from the rootstalk of the May apple (<spn>Podophyllum
peltatum</spn>). It is a complex mixture of several
substances.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Podophyllous</ent>⟦br⟧
